    ("How do you communicate during an AI security incident?", "Communication during AI incidents should follow predefined escalation paths, use clear severity levels, provide regular status updates to stakeholders, avoid technical jargon for business audiences, document all communications, and include AI-specific context about model behavior and impact."),
    ("What is model rollback and when should you use it?", "Model rollback reverts to a previously deployed model version when the current model is compromised or malfunctioning. Use it when adversarial attacks are detected, unexpected behavior emerges, performance degrades significantly, or a backdoor is discovered in the current model."),
    ("How do you prevent alert fatigue in AI monitoring?", "Reduce alert fatigue by tuning detection thresholds based on operational experience, implementing alert correlation and deduplication, prioritizing alerts by severity and business impact, using contextual enrichment to reduce false positives, and regularly reviewing and retiring outdated rules."),
