    ("What is drift detection and why is it important for security?", "Drift detection identifies when incoming data or model predictions shift from training baselines. It's security-relevant because adversarial attacks, data poisoning, and model degradation all manifest as drift. Detecting drift early enables rapid response before significant impact occurs."),
    ("How do you coordinate between AI teams and security teams during incidents?", "Coordination requires pre-established communication channels, shared incident taxonomies, joint training exercises, clear role definitions (AI team assesses model impact while security team handles infrastructure), shared dashboards, and regular cross-team meetings to maintain collaboration readiness."),
